OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1783703991
OL,3,CLondon mayor's office blocking Met
OL,4,Cdeal was unlawful, court documents
OL,5,Cclaim
OL,7,FThe Met had sought approval for the
OL,8,Fdeal to provide artificial
OL,9,Fintelligence technology to automate
OL,10,Fintelligence analysis in criminal
OL,11,Finvestigations, with AI technology
OL,12,Falready available to other forces, the
OL,13,FNHS and the Ministry of Defence.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/13
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1783703991
OL,3,CLondon mayor's office blocking Met
OL,4,Cdeal was unlawful, court documents
OL,5,Cclaim
OL,7,FBut Mopac blocked the move, claiming
OL,8,Fthat Palantir was the only supplier
OL,9,Fthe Met had seriously considered for
OL,10,Fthe proposed contract, and the force
OL,11,Ffailed to present its procurement
OL,12,Fstrategy to Mopac for approval in a
OL,13,F"clear and serious breach" of
OL,14,Fprocedure, meaning City Hall could not
OL,15,Fensure value for money.
OL,17,FAfter the decision in May, the force
OL,18,Fwarned that it would have to reduce
OL,19,Fofficer numbers, with Palantir's UK
OL,20,Fchief executive claiming Sir Sadiq was
OL,21,F"putting politics over public safety".
OL,26,@uD@AOUuD@ZO]}D@AOU}D@eO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/13
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1783703991
OL,3,CLondon mayor's office blocking Met
OL,4,Cdeal was unlawful, court documents
OL,5,Cclaim
OL,7,FPalantir then filed a legal claim
OL,8,Fagainst Mopac at the High Court in
OL,9,FJune, with lawyers for the company
OL,10,Fclaiming in court documents that it is
OL,11,Fseeking "a declaration that (Mopac)
OL,12,Fhas acted unlawfully, an order
OL,13,Fquashing the decision, and an order
OL,14,Fthat the contract be awarded to the
OL,15,Fclaimant".
OL,17,FMopac, which is due to file defence to
OL,18,Fthe claim later this month, has said
OL,19,Fit will oppose the action.
OL,26,@sD@IOUwD@IO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/13
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1783703991
OL,3,CLondon mayor's office blocking Met
OL,4,Cdeal was unlawful, court documents
OL,5,Cclaim
OL,7,FAt a preliminary hearing on Thursday,
OL,8,FMr Justice Constable said that a full
OL,9,Fhearing in the case would take place
OL,10,Fin January next year.
OL,12,FIn court documents setting out
OL,13,FPalantir's claim, Lord Pannick KC said
OL,14,Fthat the Met approached the company
OL,15,Fabout the contract in April, and
OL,16,Funderstood that it had been selected
OL,17,Fas the supplier by May.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G5/13
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1783703991
OL,3,CLondon mayor's office blocking Met
OL,4,Cdeal was unlawful, court documents
OL,5,Cclaim
OL,7,FBut Lord Pannick said that press
OL,8,Farticles on Mopac's refusal to approve
OL,9,Fthe deal cited concerns about
OL,10,FPalantir's values and ethics.
OL,12,FThese included a Guardian article in
OL,13,FApril quoting a spokesperson for the
OL,14,FMayor of London's office who said: "As
OL,15,Fa general point, the mayor would have
OL,16,Fconcerns about using public money to
OL,17,Fsupport firms who act contrary to
OL,18,FLondon's values."
OL,26,@vD@dOUzD@QO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G6/13
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1783703991
OL,3,CLondon mayor's office blocking Met
OL,4,Cdeal was unlawful, court documents
OL,5,Cclaim
OL,7,FThe barrister also said that in June,
OL,8,Fthe Met said in a public response to
OL,9,FMopac's decision that it "made best
OL,10,Fendeavours to repeatedly engage
OL,11,F(Mopac)" throughout the procurement
OL,12,Fprocess, and that Palantir offered the
OL,13,Fonly "viable service offering capable
OL,14,Fof meeting the specific requirements"
OL,15,Fof the contract.
OL,26,@qD@ZOUsD@HO]uD@FOUvD@eO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G7/13
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1783703991
OL,3,CLondon mayor's office blocking Met
OL,4,Cdeal was unlawful, court documents
OL,5,Cclaim
OL,7,FHe continued that Mopac's assessment
OL,8,Fof Palantir's "values and ethics" had
OL,9,Fplayed an "unlawful and non-
OL,10,Ftransparent role" in the decision-
OL,11,Fmaking process, claiming that Mopac
OL,12,Fhas "not acted transparently in
OL,13,Fdisclosing the correct or complete
OL,14,Freasons for the decision".
OL,16,FLord Pannick said that the "irrelevant
OL,17,Fconsideration" of Palantir's supposed
OL,18,Fvalues and ethics was a "manifest
OL,19,Ferror" and meant that Mopac unlawfully
OL,20,Fdiscriminated against the company
OL,21,Fwhile introducing an "unlawful veto".
OL,26,@pD@OOUpD@aO]qD@KOUrD@QO]tD@EOUvD@YO]xD@
OL,26,A\OUyD@NO]zD@YOU{D@FO]}D@VOU}D@dO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G8/13
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37509
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1783703991
OL,3,CLondon mayor's office blocking Met
OL,4,Cdeal was unlawful, court documents
OL,5,Cclaim
OL,7,FHe continued that this meant the
OL,8,Fdecision was "irrational,
OL,9,Fdisproportionate, and is based on
OL,10,Firrelevant considerations".
OL,12,FHe also said that Mopac's claim that
OL,13,Fits decision was based on the Met not
OL,14,Finforming it of the force's
OL,15,Fprocurement strategy and that the deal
OL,16,Fdid not represent value for money was
OL,17,F"manifestly erroneous".
OL,26,@pD@NOUrD@ZO]yD@AOUyD@VO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G9/13
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37510
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1783703991
OL,3,CLondon mayor's office blocking Met
OL,4,Cdeal was unlawful, court documents
OL,5,Cclaim
OL,7,FHe said: "It is... inherently
OL,8,Fimplausible that the selection of
OL,9,FPalantir as the 'best, and/or most
OL,10,Feconomical' supplier was incorrect:
OL,11,Fthe Met has adopted a robust and
OL,12,Feffective process, advised by
OL,13,Fspecialist procurement lawyers and
OL,14,Fconsultants."
OL,26,@oD@JOUvD@MO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G10/13
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
